// Track 10 M3a floor probe (techdesign-threads-3 §2): exercise the capability-
// probe seam DIRECTLY on the serial reference engines before anything is built
// on it — the cheap de-risk a sibling track's IR-lowering surprise argues for.
// sysThreadStart is the probe: it returns -1 where there are no true threads
// (the interpreters), which is what routes prelude `spawn` to its cooperative
// loop-task leg. (sysThreadResult is never reached on this leg — the -1 path
// registers no watch — so it has nothing to probe here; its true-thread lowering
// is covered on LLVM at M3c.)
int jfd = std::sysThreadStart(() => 6 * 7);
console.writeln(jfd);              // -1 : no true threads on the serial engines
console.writeln(jfd < 0);         // true : so spawn takes the cooperative leg
